reviews.title: Great location
reviews.text: Wonderful location right next to the canal. The staff were very friendly and told us about the history of the area as well. Food was freshly prepared and very tasty.

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

articleContent.title: Weekend in Lake Havasu: an incredible shoreline and many outdoor activities

seoInfo.metaDescription: Has a vacation ever been so epic that you thought, “I could live here”? That’s exactly how Gina and Bob Strasbaugh felt when they visited Lake Havasu, Arizona. They fell in love with the massive waterfront, the outdoor activities, and the endless sun (a whopping 300 days of it a year). So, they did what any rational person would do: They moved there permanently.

articleContent.title: A food lover’s guide to North Myrtle Beach

seoInfo.metaDescription: Whether it’s shoulder season or summer’s peak, you’ll always find delicious dishes at North Myrtle Beach. Dine by the waterfront after a balmy beach day, eat like the locals at treasured hotspots, or take the family out for a celebratory meal. Whatever you crave in an unforgettable vacation, you’re sure to find it here in this must-read roundup of top restaurants.

articleContent.title: Your go-to stay to take care of business

seoInfo.metaDescription: Business travel calls for a hotel that can serve as your office on the go and home away from home, so choosing the right stay is top priority. Fortunately, finding the right fit is easier than you think when you go with a trusted name. From comfortable workspaces to perfect locations, discover why professionals choose Radisson hotels for the trips that matter most.

tripContent.title: Orlando: An LGBTQ+ family guide
tripContent.description: "Our family loves going to Orlando—and not just for the theme parks. Yes, we enjoy getting to ride rollercoasters and be transported to another world, but spending time in a colorful, diverse city and the surrounding nature is delightful. We live just over an hour from Orlando, so when we feel the need for good city vibes and to feel welcome in a neighborhood besides our own, Orlando is a fantastic option for us." - Rob Taylor, 2TravelDads.com

articleContent.title: Start here: these hotels will inspire your entire trip

seoInfo.metaDescription: When choosing a stay for your long-awaited vacation, the usual checklist comes to mind: good location, comfy room, and, if you’re lucky, a pool. But if the goal of your getaway is to explore someplace new, shouldn’t you expect cultural experiences and local flavor from your hotel, too?

tripContent.title: Celebrate Nevada's history, rhythm, and culture
tripContent.description: Nevada’s story is etched in historic mining towns, roadside wonders, galleries, and museums. From frontier heritage and atomic relics to glowing neon art, every stop reveals a new layer of the state's past and present. Whether you're wandering small-town streets or stepping into iconic city museums, this journey blends memory and motion in a way that’s anything but ordinary.

articleContent.title: Best areas to stay in Marrakech to get a real feel for the city

seoInfo.metaDescription: I still remember the morning I went rug shopping in Marrakech and ended up eating homemade couscous with the shopkeeper and his wife. What started as a quick errand turned into an afternoon of stories and genuine connection. And years later, we're still friends. That's Marrakech for you—a city where a simple purchase can turn into a lifelong friendship. I ended up living in the city for  three years, exploring the city's incredible blend of African, Arab, and European influences evident in its architecture, markets, and cuisine.
